  "prompt": "What is \u2018double diameter\u2019 in a circle?",
  "response": "The term \"double diameter\" in the context of a circle refers to twice the length of the diameter. The diameter of a circle is the straight line passing through the center that connects two points on the circumference. If you double the length of this line, you get the \"double diameter.\" Mathematically, if the diameter of a circle is denoted as \\( d \\), then the double diameter is \\( 2d \\). This measurement is simply twice the distance across the circle, passing through its center.",
